<plot>The short documentary "Sprawl" takes a look at our societies rapid growth and urban sprawl in our communities and the effect that it has not only on our environment, but on our everyday lives as a whole. It is a introspective view into our obsession with bigger, better, newer and middle class Americas longing for a Suburban Utopia, littered with gated communities, and landscaped lawns.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?511485</url></doc>
